The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Metro | Duo held for fraud
                                                                                                               Duo held for fraud
          A STAFF REPORTER                               
	A 65-year-old postal agent and his 46-year-old nephew were arrested on Wednesday for allegedly defrauding elderly investors in post office monthly income schemes by offering to fill up their forms.         
	Manoranjan Dey is an agent at Ballygunge post office while his nephew Bapi Dey used to assist him.         
	Nivash Chowdhury, a Santoshpur resident, complained to police that the two had forged his signature and withdrawn around Rs 3.5 lakh from his account between March 2006 and May 2007.                                                                                                                                                                            
